-Well, it's not too bad.
-No.

16:28.112 --> 16:30.364
No. I can just get a brush
and smooth it over.

16:30.530 --> 16:32.741
-I think we're okay.
-Is that the only spot?

16:32.907 --> 16:36.203
-Where else did we do it?
-Let me see.

16:36.370 --> 16:41.166
Okay, we started here, right,
and then we took it over here.

16:41.333 --> 16:42.792
We brought it to....

16:44.753 --> 16:46.255
Uh-oh.

16:49.966 --> 16:51.968
JENNIFER: Is that--
-Yup.

16:52.136 --> 16:54.013
That's your butt.

16:54.221 --> 16:55.430
[♪♪♪]

16:56.140 --> 16:59.559
So then the first cowboy says--
Heh, heh, heh.

16:59.726 --> 17:01.978
"No, no, no. I said, posse."

17:02.146 --> 17:04.148
[ALL LAUGHING]

17:06.941 --> 17:08.902
What's the matter, Russell?

17:09.069 --> 17:12.906
Don't you get it?
You see, "posse" sounds like--

17:13.073 --> 17:15.075
No, no, no. I know, I know, I know.

17:16.118 --> 17:18.870
It's very clever. That's a good one.

17:19.038 --> 17:20.455
Are you having any fun?

17:20.622 --> 17:23.958
Well, not the kind of fun
I was hoping to have.

17:25.669 --> 17:27.754
And don't get me wrong,
you guys are great.

17:27.921 --> 17:28.922
I mean, Pearl...

17:29.089 --> 17:31.425
...if you were 100 years younger,
I mean, who knows?

17:34.636 --> 17:37.097
But aren't there any young chicks
on this raft?

17:37.264 --> 17:40.059
Oh, yes. Younger.

17:40.225 --> 17:41.810
-Younger?
SILVIA: Yeah.

17:41.976 --> 17:43.978
We got a couple gals in our group.

17:44.146 --> 17:46.981
See, if they're under 50,
they wear pink hats.

17:47.899 --> 17:49.318
Pink hats.

17:49.901 --> 17:52.196
Well, okay.

17:53.072 --> 17:54.864
Pink hats....

17:59.703 --> 18:03.832
Aha. Okay. Excuse me, one second.

18:07.419 --> 18:09.796
Well, hello, there, youngish lady.

18:18.054 --> 18:20.974
Well, hello, Russell.

18:22.058 --> 18:23.059
Oh, for--

18:23.227 --> 18:24.228
[SHIP HORN BLOWS]

18:24.394 --> 18:25.687
--sakes.

18:25.895 --> 18:27.897
[♪♪♪]

18:32.194 --> 18:33.737
Well, maybe I'll just leave then.

18:34.821 --> 18:35.947
Oh, yeah, thanks a lot.

18:36.740 --> 18:38.242
-What?
-Your little video idea...

18:38.408 --> 18:39.909
...just made things worse.

18:40.076 --> 18:42.329
Look, let's not shift the blame to me.

18:43.122 --> 18:46.082
Clearly you both have some
deep-seated resentments
toward each other.

18:46.250 --> 18:49.711
-Yeah, we're married.
-And I could've done better. Go on.

18:49.878 --> 18:52.046
Anyway, there's work to be done.

18:52.214 --> 18:54.299
If you truly want
your relationship to grow...

18:54.466 --> 18:56.551
...then you're going to need
to communicate better.

18:56.926 --> 18:59.554
So I suggest getting out
those emotional shovels...

18:59.721 --> 19:02.391
...and digging until you uncover
everything that needs to be said.

19:02.974 --> 19:04.893
I'll leave you to it.

19:08.104 --> 19:09.356
Wow.

19:09.523 --> 19:13.527
-He really laid it out there, didn't he?
-Yeah, I guess so.

19:13.693 --> 19:16.029
Quite a bit to think about.

19:17.364 --> 19:18.990
[AUDREY SIGHS]

19:19.366 --> 19:21.451
Sounds like a lot of work, doesn't it?

19:21.618 --> 19:24.704
A lot. Plus it's Timmy,
for crying out loud.

19:24.871 --> 19:27.999
-What does he know?
-We've been married for 16 years.

19:28.167 --> 19:29.709
I think we kind of know
what we're doing.

19:29.876 --> 19:32.712
[IMITATING TIMMY] "I suggest
you get out your emotional shovels."

19:32.879 --> 19:35.965
Yeah, shovel this, pal.

19:36.841 --> 19:38.092
Idiot.

19:38.260 --> 19:39.719
[JEFF LAUGHING]

19:39.886 --> 19:42.681
I really must stop
trying to help people.

19:42.972 --> 19:44.391
[♪♪♪]

19:44.558 --> 19:46.100
Okay, thank you. Thanks.

19:46.268 --> 19:48.562
So the upholstery place said
they can fix it by tonight...

19:48.728 --> 19:52.106
-...but we have to get it there right now.
-But the cushions are sewn in.

19:52.274 --> 19:54.359
We'd have to bring the whole chair
and it's big.

19:54.526 --> 19:57.321
Hey, they got it in, we can get it out.

20:00.114 --> 20:02.116
How did they get it in?

20:03.327 --> 20:05.745
I don't know,
but we've gotta do something.

20:05.912 --> 20:08.540
Okay, okay, let me just think
for a second.

20:08.707 --> 20:09.708
[SIGHS]

20:09.874 --> 20:12.586
JEFF [IN HIGH-PITCHED VOICE]:
"Sweep your chimney for you, governor?"

20:12.752 --> 20:14.379
[AUDREY LAUGHING]

20:15.922 --> 20:17.674
ADAM:
Okay, how about this?

20:17.841 --> 20:19.259
We put the chair back...

20:19.426 --> 20:21.010
...and we cover the paint
with a Sharpie.

20:21.177 --> 20:24.473
I mean, the way Jeff drinks,
he'll never know the difference.

20:26.099 --> 20:27.976
Oh, hey, guys.

20:28.810 --> 20:33.064
Oh, I closed your windows,
just like you asked.

20:33.732 --> 20:35.734
[♪♪♪]

20:50.790 --> 20:53.793
Oh, it's so beautifully designed.

20:54.586 --> 20:56.671
And the way the light flickers off it...

20:56.838 --> 20:58.840
...I just hope I can do it justice.

20:59.758 --> 21:02.677
Yeah, try to do a good job
on the necklace too.

21:04.304 --> 21:06.306
[♪♪♪]

21:11.395 --> 21:13.397
[♪♪♪]
